stylometry:
When managing inventory, you have to look at the costs associated with this. The costs included are inventory costs, holding/carrying costs, ordering costs, safety stock costs, and stock out costs. There is a trade-off betweeen the quantity, holding costs, and ordering costs:
The greater the quantity, the lower the ordering costs
The smaller the quantity, the lower the holding costs. 
Management has to find the tradeoff that maximizes customer satisfaction whild minimizing the all of the costs.
